HEADWORD: Porte
<hw>Porte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>porte</ets> a
gate, L. <ets>porta</ets>. See <er>Port</er> a gate.]</ety> <def>The
Ottoman court; the government of the Turkish empire, officially called
the <altname>Sublime Porte</altname>, from the gate (<xex>port</xex>) of
the sultan's palace at which justice was administered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

